2.) Error:CREATE TABLE django_migrations...
    problem: created a user without assigning ownership and grant create priviledges
    infomation: PostgreSQL default behavior is strict
                By default:
                 - public schema allows limited actions
                 - only postgres (admin) has full rights
                 - new users are “guests”
    FIX:
        - ALTER SCHEMA public OWNER TO airbnb_user;
        - GRANT ALL ON SCHEMA public TO airbnb_user;
        - GRANT CREATE ON SCHEMA public TO airbnb_user;

        i.)ALTER SCHEMA public OWNER TO airbnb_user;
            This made your user the boss of the schema Now it can:
                - create tables
                - modify tables
                - manage objects
        ii.)GRANT ALL ON SCHEMA public TO airbnb_user;
                - This gives full operational rights inside schema
        iii.)GRANT CREATE ON SCHEMA public TO airbnb_user;
                - 👉 This specifically unlocked:
                    - CREATE TABLE
                    - CREATE INDEX
                    - migrations
                -PRACTICE 1: Always set schema ownership when creating DB

    How to NEVER get this error again (BEST PRACTICES):
        ✅ PRACTICE 1: Always set schema ownership when creating DB
        When setting up PostgreSQL:
            - CREATE DATABASE airbnb_db;
            - CREATE USER airbnb_user WITH PASSWORD 'xxx';
            - ALTER DATABASE airbnb_db OWNER TO airbnb_user;
        
        ✅ PRACTICE 2: Always set schema permissions immediately
        After creating DB:
            - ALTER SCHEMA public OWNER TO airbnb_user;
            - GRANT ALL ON SCHEMA public TO airbnb_user;
        
        ✅ PRACTICE 3: Use ONE dedicated DB user per project
        Avoid:
            - using postgres user in Django ❌
            - sharing DB users across projects ❌

        Correct:
            - airbnb_user
            - blog_user
            - ecommerce_user

        ✅ PRACTICE 4: Always test permissions BEFORE Django
            - Before running migrations:
            - CREATE TABLE test_table(id INT);
            - If this fails → Django will fail too.
        ✅ PRACTICE 5: Use .env for credentials (VERY IMPORTANT for AWS)